Section 1:
SR 27 Text skip navigation SENATE PRESIDENT SENATORS COMMITTEES VIDEO/AUDIO DISTRICT MAPS SENATE CLERK SENATE RULES HOUSE SPEAKER DELEGATES COMMITTEES VIDEO/AUDIO DISTRICT MAPS HOUSE CLERK HOUSE RULES HOUSE STAFF JOINT INTERIM COMMITTEES LEGISLATIVE ADMINISTRATOR LEGISLATIVE SERVICES DIVISION PUBLIC INFORMATION LEGISLATIVE AUTOMATED SYSTEMS DIVISION LEGISLATIVE AUDITOR'S OFFICE PERFORMANCE EVALUATION & RESEARCH DIVISION POST AUDIT DIVISION BUDGET DIVISION REGULATORY AND FISCAL AFFAIRS DIVISION CLAIMS COMMISSION CRIME VICTIMS RULE-MAKING REVIEW SPECIAL INVESTIGATIONS JUDICIAL COMP. COMMISSION JOINT RULES STAFF INFO BILL STATUS BILL STATUS BILL TRACKING STATE LAW WEST VIRGINIA CODE ACTS OF THE LEGISLATURE CODE OF 1931 WV CONSTITUTION US CONSTITUTION REPORTS AGENCY REPORTS AGENCY GRANT AWARDS PERFORMANCE EVALUATIONS POST AUDITS EDUCATIONAL CITIZEN’S GUIDE INTERNSHIP PROGRAM PAGE PROGRAM PUBLICATIONS PHOTO GALLERY CAPITOL HISTORY HOW A BILL BECOMES LAW CONTACT SENATE ROSTER HOUSE ROSTER PUBLIC INFO. NEWS RELEASES HELPFUL LINKS Introduced Version Senate Resolution 27 History |  Email Key: Green = existing Code. Red = new code to be enacted SENATE RESOLUTION 27(By Senators Taylor, Martin, and Jeffries)[Introduced March 12, 2025] Congratulating the Taylor County Middle school football team for winning the 2024 Mid-8 Championship.Whereas, The Taylor County Middle school football team created history on October 30, 2024, when the Knights claimed their first ever Mid-8 Championship in a 54-20 win; andWhereas, The Taylor County Middle school football team had a remarkable year on the gridiron resulting in a 9-0 season that qualified them for the Mid-8 Championship playoffs where they won making it the first win in the school’s 31-year program history following a previous three-year attempt for the championship; andWhereas, The Knights football team is led by head coach Bobby Beltner who credits the success to all the players through their hard work and perseverance, and the dedication of the volunteer coaching staff which includes Sam Jones, Junior Lambert, Jamen Summers, Keith Hodges, Anthony Forte, Brian Lough, Cameron Forte, and Jaron Freeman; andWhereas, Head coach Bobby Beltner is to be commended for his firm belief in the value of the program and keeping each player encouraged and engaged to help them benefit from the value of belonging to a team; andWhereas, The 2024 Knights football team is a shining example to all West Virginians of what can be accomplished with dedication, commitment, and teamwork, and will be remembered as one of the best teams ever assembled in West Virginia middle school football history; therefore, be itResolved by the Senate:That the Senate hereby congratulates the Taylor County Middle School Knights for winning the 2024 Mid-8 Championship; and, be itFurther Resolved, That the Senate commends the team and the coaches for their unwavering determination and grit for their outstanding accomplishment; and, be itFurther Resolved, That the Clerk is hereby directed to forward a copy of this resolution to the Taylor County Middle School football team. Bill Status  | Bill Tracking  | Legacy WV Code  | Bulletin Board  | District Maps  | Senate Roster  | House Roster  | Live  | Blog  | Jobs  | Links  | Home This Web site is maintained by the West Virginia Legislature's Office of Reference & Information.  | Terms of Use | Webmaster | © 2025 West Virginia Legislature ** Print On Demand Name: Email: Phone:


